---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="System Integration | Intelio - Connect Your Systems" description="Connect fragmented business systems so information flows automatically instead of being manually copied between platforms.">
<main class="bg-white">
  <!-- HERO SECTION: Video Background -->
  <section class="relative h-[600px] md:h-[450px] sm:h-[300px] flex items-center justify-center overflow-hidden bg-black">
    <!-- Video Background -->
    <video 
      autoplay
      muted
      loop
      playsinline
      preload="auto"
      class="absolute inset-0 w-full h-full object-cover"
    >
      <source src="/videos/system-integration-hero.mp4" type="video/mp4">
      Your browser does not support the video tag.
    </video>
    
    <!-- Dark Overlay for Text Readability -->
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-black/45 z-[1]"></div>

    <!-- Hero Content -->
    <div class="relative z-10 max-w-4xl mx-auto px-[6%] text-center">
      <h1 class="text-[48px] md:text-[36px] sm:text-[24px] text-white mb-6 leading-[1.2] font-normal tracking-[-0.5px]">
        Systems Stay in Sync Automatically
      </h1>
      <p class="text-lg md:text-base sm:text-sm text-[#d1d5db] leading-[1.7] font-normal max-w-[600px] mx-auto mb-10">
        Data entered once. Propagates everywhere. No re-entry. No manual coordination. No bottleneck.
      </p>
      <a href="/contact" class="inline-block px-7 py-3 bg-white text-black text-[15px] font-normal hover:bg-gray-100 transition-colors rounded-md border border-white">
        Start a Project
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="max-w-[1200px] mx-auto px-[6%]">
    <!-- THE PROBLEM SECTION -->
    <section class="pt-20 pb-20 border-t border-gray-200">
      <h2 class="text-[32px] md:text-[28px] sm:text-[24px] text-black mb-4 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
        What's Broken Today
      </h2>
      <p class="text-base text-gray-600 leading-[1.8] mb-12 font-normal max-w-[700px]">
        Most businesses run on disconnected systems. Data lives in silos. Someone is responsible for keeping everything in sync.
      </p>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 mb-10">
        <div class="p-0">
          <h3 class="text-lg text-black mb-3 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            Manual Data Replication
          </h3>
          <p class="text-[15px] text-gray-600 leading-[1.7] font-normal">
            Customer data entered in CRM, re-entered in accounting, re-entered in project management. Same person. Multiple systems. Hours per week wasted.
          </p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="p-0">
          <h3 class="text-lg text-black mb-3 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            Disconnected Workflows
          </h3>
          <p class="text-[15px] text-gray-600 leading-[1.7] font-normal">
            Deal closes in CRM but finance doesn't know. Project completes but accounting doesn't see it. Information moves in silos, not synchronized.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="p-0">
          <h3 class="text-lg text-black mb-3 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            System Conflicts
          </h3>
          <p class="text-[15px] text-gray-600 leading-[1.7] font-normal">
            Different systems show different customer data. Finance sees one version, operations sees another. Decisions made on conflicting information.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="p-0">
          <h3 class="text-lg text-black mb-3 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            No Single Source of Truth
          </h3>
          <p class="text-[15px] text-gray-600 leading-[1.7] font-normal">
            Customer address lives in three places. Which one is right? Nobody knows. Financial reconciliation becomes guesswork.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- WHAT CHANGES SECTION -->
    <section class="pt-20 pb-20 border-t border-gray-200">
      <h2 class="text-[32px] md:text-[28px] sm:text-[24px] text-black mb-4 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
        What Changes After Deployment
      </h2>
      <p class="text-base text-gray-600 leading-[1.8] mb-12 font-normal max-w-[700px]">
        The system removes coordination overhead by making data flow automatic instead of manual.
      </p>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-5">
        <div class="p-8 bg-[#f0f9ff] border-l-[3px] border-[#3b82f6] rounded">
          <h3 class="text-base text-black mb-3 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            Automatic Information Flow
          </h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-[1.7] font-normal">
            Data entered once, propagates everywhere automatically. No re-entry. No manual copying. No human bottleneck.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="p-8 bg-[#f0f9ff] border-l-[3px] border-[#3b82f6] rounded">
          <h3 class="text-base text-black mb-3 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            Real-Time Synchronization
          </h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-[1.7] font-normal">
            Deal closes at 4 PM. Invoice exists in accounting by 4:15 PM. One source of truth, updated as events happen.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="p-8 bg-[#f0f9ff] border-l-[3px] border-[#3b82f6] rounded">
          <h3 class="text-base text-black mb-3 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            Built-In Conflict Detection
          </h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-[1.7] font-normal">
            System detects when data diverges across systems and alerts you before decisions get made on bad information.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="p-8 bg-[#f0f9ff] border-l-[3px] border-[#3b82f6] rounded">
          <h3 class="text-base text-black mb-3 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            Time Freed for Revenue Work
          </h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-[1.7] font-normal">
            The person whose job was syncing systems? That 10-15 hours per week is now available for core business work.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="p-8 bg-[#f0f9ff] border-l-[3px] border-[#3b82f6] rounded md:col-span-2 lg:col-span-1">
          <h3 class="text-base text-black mb-3 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            Complete Audit Trail
          </h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-[1.7] font-normal">
            Every data movement recorded. Who updated what. When it changed. Why it moved. Compliance and debugging become straightforward.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- HOW IT WORKS SECTION -->
    <section class="pt-20 pb-20 border-t border-gray-200">
      <h2 class="text-[32px] md:text-[28px] sm:text-[24px] text-black mb-4 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
        How the System Actually Works
      </h2>
      <p class="text-base text-gray-600 leading-[1.8] mb-12 font-normal max-w-[700px]">
        The system monitors your business systems for changes, applies your rules, executes actions, and keeps humans in control.
      </p>

      <div class="mb-10">
        <div class="p-8 border border-gray-200 border-t rounded-t-lg bg-white">
          <h3 class="text-[15px] text-black mb-3 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            Input Layer
          </h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-[1.7] font-normal">
            Your data already exists in systems you operate (CRM, accounting, project management). The integration continuously monitors for changes: new records created, existing records modified, status transitions, financial transactions.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="p-8 border-x border-gray-200 bg-white">
          <h3 class="text-[15px] text-black mb-3 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            Decision Logic
          </h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-[1.7] font-normal">
            The system applies rules you define. Where should this data go? How should it be formatted for the target system? If data exists in multiple places, which version is authoritative? What conditions require human review?
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="p-8 border-x border-gray-200 bg-white">
          <h3 class="text-[15px] text-black mb-3 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            Action Layer
          </h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-[1.7] font-normal">
            Based on the logic, the system executes automatically. Creates or updates records in target systems. Sends notifications when data moves. Triggers downstream workflows. Generates audit logs with complete records of what moved, when, and why.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="p-8 border border-gray-200 border-b rounded-b-lg bg-white">
          <h3 class="text-[15px] text-black mb-3 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            Oversight Layer
          </h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-[1.7] font-normal">
            Humans stay in control. The system routes exceptions to people when needed. Requires approval for sensitive operations if configured. Provides dashboards showing what moved, what failed, what needs attention. Can be paused immediately. Can be reconfigured as business rules change.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- PROOF OF PRODUCTION REALITY -->
    <section class="pt-20 pb-20 border-t border-gray-200">
      <h2 class="text-[32px] md:text-[28px] sm:text-[24px] text-black mb-4 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
        This Actually Works
      </h2>
      <p class="text-base text-gray-600 leading-[1.8] mb-12 font-normal max-w-[700px]">
        These aren't theoretical concepts. This is infrastructure running in production right now.
      </p>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-8 mb-12">
        <div class="p-8 bg-gradient-to-br from-[#f8fafc] to-[#f1f5f9] rounded-lg border border-[#e2e8f0]">
          <h3 class="text-[28px] text-[#1e40af] mb-2 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            50-100
          </h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-2 leading-[1.6] font-normal">
            Data sync operations per day across current deployments
          </p>
          <p class="text-[13px] text-gray-500 mt-2 font-normal">
            Running continuously. Zero unplanned downtime in 60+ days.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="p-8 bg-gradient-to-br from-[#f8fafc] to-[#f1f5f9] rounded-lg border border-[#e2e8f0]">
          <h3 class="text-[28px] text-[#1e40af] mb-2 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            5-15
          </h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-2 leading-[1.6] font-normal">
            System-to-system connections per client
          </p>
          <p class="text-[13px] text-gray-500 mt-2 font-normal">
            Handling real-world complexity: validation, error recovery, escalation.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="p-8 bg-gradient-to-br from-[#f8fafc] to-[#f1f5f9] rounded-lg border border-[#e2e8f0]">
          <h3 class="text-[28px] text-[#1e40af] mb-2 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            10-15 hrs/week
          </h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-2 leading-[1.6] font-normal">
            Time freed from manual data coordination
          </p>
          <p class="text-[13px] text-gray-500 mt-2 font-normal">
            Per client. That's one person's job eliminated and capacity freed for revenue work.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="p-8 bg-gradient-to-br from-[#f8fafc] to-[#f1f5f9] rounded-lg border border-[#e2e8f0]">
          <h3 class="text-[28px] text-[#1e40af] mb-2 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            Same-Day
          </h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-2 leading-[1.6] font-normal">
            Financial reconciliation time
          </p>
          <p class="text-[13px] text-gray-500 mt-2 font-normal">
            Down from 3-5 days. Because data flows automatically instead of waiting for someone to copy it.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="p-8 bg-[#f9fafb] border border-gray-200 rounded-lg">
        <h3 class="text-base text-black mb-4 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
          Mission-Critical Operations
        </h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-black leading-[1.6] mb-4 font-normal">
          Integrations aren't optional. They're what runs your business.
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-sm text-gray-600 list-none">
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span class="text-[#3b82f6] mr-3 font-normal">→</span>
            <span class="font-normal leading-[1.6]">Financial reconciliation depends on data flowing from operations to accounting</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span class="text-[#3b82f6] mr-3 font-normal">→</span>
            <span class="font-normal leading-[1.6]">Revenue recognition depends on deal data syncing from CRM to financial systems</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span class="text-[#3b82f6] mr-3 font-normal">→</span>
            <span class="font-normal leading-[1.6]">Project profitability depends on cost data flowing from operations to finance</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span class="text-[#3b82f6] mr-3 font-normal">→</span>
            <span class="font-normal leading-[1.6]">Customer experience depends on customer data staying synchronized</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ENGAGEMENT MODELS SECTION -->
    <section class="pt-20 pb-20 border-t border-gray-200">
      <h2 class="text-[32px] md:text-[28px] sm:text-[24px] text-black mb-4 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
        How We Work
      </h2>
      <p class="text-base text-gray-600 leading-[1.8] mb-12 font-normal max-w-[700px]">
        Two engagement models. Clear ownership. Explicit responsibilities.
      </p>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 mb-10">
        <div class="p-10 border-2 border-gray-200 rounded-lg bg-white">
          <h3 class="text-lg text-black mb-2 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            Build + Maintain
          </h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-6 italic font-normal">
            You own operations. We monitor and optimize.
          </p>
          
          <div class="space-y-4 mb-6">
            <div>
              <p class="text-[13px] text-black mb-1.5 font-normal uppercase tracking-wider">You Own</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-[1.6] font-normal">Day-to-day decisions about data flows and business rules</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="text-[13px] text-black mb-1.5 font-normal uppercase tracking-wider">We Own</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-[1.6] font-normal">System monitoring, performance tuning, infrastructure health</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="p-4 bg-[#f0f9ff] rounded-md mb-4 border-l-[3px] border-[#3b82f6]">
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-[1.6] font-normal">
              <span class="font-normal">Best for:</span> You have an operations or IT team that can own the workflow. You want monthly support, not daily operational involvement.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="text-[13px] text-gray-500 mt-5 pt-4 border-t border-gray-200 font-normal">Project fee + monthly maintenance</div>
        </div>

        <div class="p-10 border-2 border-gray-200 rounded-lg bg-white">
          <h3 class="text-lg text-black mb-2 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            Build + Operate
          </h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-6 italic font-normal">
            We embed and manage the system end-to-end.
          </p>
          
          <div class="space-y-4 mb-6">
            <div>
              <p class="text-[13px] text-black mb-1.5 font-normal uppercase tracking-wider">You Own</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-[1.6] font-normal">Overall business outcomes and strategy</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="text-[13px] text-black mb-1.5 font-normal uppercase tracking-wider">We Own</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-[1.6] font-normal">Daily operations, monitoring, optimization, exception handling, business rule updates</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="p-4 bg-[#f0f9ff] rounded-md mb-4 border-l-[3px] border-[#3b82f6]">
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-[1.6] font-normal">
              <span class="font-normal">Best for:</span> You want the integrations to "just work" without your team managing them. You need someone accountable for data accuracy end-to-end.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="text-[13px] text-gray-500 mt-5 pt-4 border-t border-gray-200 font-normal">Monthly operating retainer</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="p-8 bg-[#f9fafb] border border-gray-200 rounded-lg">
        <h3 class="text-base text-black mb-5 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
          What's Always Clear
        </h3>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-6">
          <div>
            <h4 class="text-[15px] text-black mb-2 font-normal leading-[1.4]">Data Ownership</h4>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-[1.6] font-normal">You own the data. We manage the pipelines. No ambiguity.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h4 class="text-[15px] text-black mb-2 font-normal leading-[1.4]">Decision Authority</h4>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-[1.6] font-normal">You control what rules the system enforces. Changes go through you.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h4 class="text-[15px] text-black mb-2 font-normal leading-[1.4]">Failure Handling</h4>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-[1.6] font-normal">If something breaks, here's who gets notified, in what order, what the rollback procedure is.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h4 class="text-[15px] text-black mb-2 font-normal leading-[1.4]">Cost Transparency</h4>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-[1.6] font-normal">Monthly costs based on systems connected, data volume, complexity. No surprises.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- COMMON PATTERNS SECTION -->
    <section class="pt-20 pb-20 border-t border-gray-200">
      <h2 class="text-[32px] md:text-[28px] sm:text-[24px] text-black mb-4 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
        Common Integration Patterns
      </h2>
      <p class="text-base text-gray-600 leading-[1.8] mb-12 font-normal max-w-[700px]">
        Real scenarios from production deployments.
      </p>

      <div class="space-y-8">
        <div class="p-8 bg-[#f9fafb] border border-gray-200 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="text-base text-black mb-5 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            CRM ↔ Accounting (Revenue Sync)
          </h3>
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-5">
            <div class="border-b border-gray-200 pb-4">
              <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1.5 font-normal uppercase tracking-wider">Input</div>
              <div class="text-sm text-black leading-[1.6] font-normal">Deal closes in CRM (marked "Closed/Won")</div>
            </div>
            <div class="border-b border-gray-200 pb-4">
              <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1.5 font-normal uppercase tracking-wider">Action</div>
              <div class="text-sm text-black leading-[1.6] font-normal">Create invoice in accounting, update CRM with reference, notify finance</div>
            </div>
            <div class="border-b border-gray-200 pb-4 md:col-span-2">
              <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1.5 font-normal uppercase tracking-wider">Removes</div>
              <div class="text-sm text-black leading-[1.6] font-normal">Someone manually creating invoices from CRM deals (2 hours/week)</div>
            </div>
            <div class="md:col-span-2">
              <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1.5 font-normal uppercase tracking-wider">Adds</div>
              <div class="text-sm text-black leading-[1.6] font-normal">Deals close at 4 PM. Invoices exist in accounting by 4:15 PM.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="p-4 bg-[#f0f9ff] rounded-md border-l-[3px] border-[#3b82f6] mt-4 md:col-span-2">
              <p class="text-sm text-black font-normal leading-[1.6]">
                <span class="font-normal">Result:</span> 100% invoice creation accuracy. Processing time instant. No manual data entry.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="p-8 bg-[#f9fafb] border border-gray-200 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="text-base text-black mb-5 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            Operations ↔ Finance (Profitability)
          </h3>
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-5">
            <div class="border-b border-gray-200 pb-4">
              <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1.5 font-normal uppercase tracking-wider">Input</div>
              <div class="text-sm text-black leading-[1.6] font-normal">Project costs updated (hours, expenses), timeline changes</div>
            </div>
            <div class="border-b border-gray-200 pb-4">
              <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1.5 font-normal uppercase tracking-wider">Action</div>
              <div class="text-sm text-black leading-[1.6] font-normal">Calculate profitability, update forecast, alert finance if margin below threshold</div>
            </div>
            <div class="border-b border-gray-200 pb-4 md:col-span-2">
              <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1.5 font-normal uppercase tracking-wider">Removes</div>
              <div class="text-sm text-black leading-[1.6] font-normal">Manual profitability calculations and financial reconciliation</div>
            </div>
            <div class="md:col-span-2">
              <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1.5 font-normal uppercase tracking-wider">Adds</div>
              <div class="text-sm text-black leading-[1.6] font-normal">Real-time margin visibility. Early warning when projects are losing money.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="p-4 bg-[#f0f9ff] rounded-md border-l-[3px] border-[#3b82f6] mt-4 md:col-span-2">
              <p class="text-sm text-black font-normal leading-[1.6]">
                <span class="font-normal">Result:</span> Problems caught before they become crises. Visibility into which projects actually make money.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="p-8 bg-[#f9fafb] border border-gray-200 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="text-base text-black mb-5 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            Customer Data ↔ Everywhere (Single Source of Truth)
          </h3>
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-5">
            <div class="border-b border-gray-200 pb-4">
              <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1.5 font-normal uppercase tracking-wider">Input</div>
              <div class="text-sm text-black leading-[1.6] font-normal">Customer info updated anywhere (CRM, accounting, support)</div>
            </div>
            <div class="border-b border-gray-200 pb-4">
              <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1.5 font-normal uppercase tracking-wider">Action</div>
              <div class="text-sm text-black leading-[1.6] font-normal">Detect change, verify validity, update everywhere it's stored</div>
            </div>
            <div class="border-b border-gray-200 pb-4 md:col-span-2">
              <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1.5 font-normal uppercase tracking-wider">Removes</div>
              <div class="text-sm text-black leading-[1.6] font-normal">Customer address in three places. Uncertainty about which is correct.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="md:col-span-2">
              <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1.5 font-normal uppercase tracking-wider">Adds</div>
              <div class="text-sm text-black leading-[1.6] font-normal">One customer address, updated automatically everywhere.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="p-4 bg-[#f0f9ff] rounded-md border-l-[3px] border-[#3b82f6] mt-4 md:col-span-2">
              <p class="text-sm text-black font-normal leading-[1.6]">
                <span class="font-normal">Result:</span> One version of truth. No duplicate records. Complete sync across all systems.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- RISK & CONTROL SECTION -->
    <section class="pt-20 pb-20 border-t border-gray-200">
      <h2 class="text-[32px] md:text-[28px] sm:text-[24px] text-black mb-4 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
        Risk, Control & Ownership
      </h2>
      <p class="text-base text-gray-600 leading-[1.8] mb-12 font-normal max-w-[700px]">
        Explicit about how we handle failure and keep you in control.
